
#intro
  %h2 Learn Martian in 3 easy steps!

  - form_for @participant, :url => experiments_url, :html => { :class => "new_participant ajax_submit" } do |f|
  
    %br
    1. Put headphones on and play the test sound.
    %br
    %br
  
    .intro_inputs
      Listen to a test word:
      %button#volume_test Play
      
      %p

      The test word...
      
      %input{"type"=>"button", "value"=>"ends with a ''p'' sound"}      
      %input{"type"=>"button", "value"=>"ends with a ''t'' sound"}      

    %br(clear="both")  

    2. Copy this code and paste it in your task:

    %br 
    %br(clear="both")  
  
  
    .intro_inputs
      %fieldset.name
        %label.strong Your ID:
        %span.static_form_field= @participant.code
        = f.hidden_field :code
      %fieldset.experiment_type{ :style => "display: #{@participant.experiment_type.nil? ? 'block' : 'none'};" }
        = f.label :experiment, "Experiment type: ", :class => "strong"
        = radio_button(:participant, :experiment_type, :variable)
        = f.label(:variable, "Variable")
        = radio_button(:participant, :experiment_type, :fixed)
        = f.label(:fixed, "Fixed")

    %br
    3. Get going!

    %br 
    %br(clear="both")  


    .intro_inputs

      %fieldset.submit= submit_tag "Continue &raquo;" #, :disabled => 'disabled'




      
/  .info
/    :textile
/      Please put your headphones on, press the "play" button to hear a sample sound, and adjust the volume to a comfortable level.
/    
/      Enter your name, #{ if @participant.experiment_type.nil? then "choose your experiment type, " end } and press the "continue" button when you are all set.  
  
    
